  "time_ut": 1656564071,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "BOI \u0d85\u0db0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2 \u0da2\u0db1\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d85\u0dad\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd8\u0dad \u0dc0\u0dd6 \u0db1\u0dc0 \u0d87\u0d9f\u0dbd\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca \u0d9a\u0db8\u0dca\u0dc4\u0dbd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "New garment factory inaugurated by BOI Director General",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Aiming at the UK children's clothing market, a new garment manufacturing factory has been opened in Ambalangoda Metiyagoda area with an investment of 3.5 million US dollars.",
        "Sri Lanka Investment Board Director General Ms. Renuka Weerakoon says that a large number of new direct jobs will be created through this and a large number of indirect jobs and service providers will be created. The director general said this while inaugurating the recently opened Deepa Garment Industry Institute.",
        "Ms. Weerakoon, who further commented, said that the investment board is working to encourage investors to reinvest in the current situation. Accordingly, the Sri Lanka Board of Investment is coordinating with the investors engaged in investing in Sri Lanka to encourage them to further expand their industries. Mrs. Weerakoon said that the Stylish Group, which is currently running five industries according to that program, has taken steps to start another company very quickly today.",
        "The Sri Lanka Board of Investment is also looking to move industries away from the capital to rural areas. This is expected to boost the economy of the rural areas as compared to the city. Especially the rural women contribute to the economic development of the country, while they also have the ability to bring strength to the economy of their households. Mrs. Weerakoon also said that through the production of this factory, an opportunity has arisen for a sister of Ambalangoda Metiyagoda to join the UK children's clothing market.",
        "Mr. Leelaratne Hatanarachchi, Chairman of Stylish Group, who spoke at this, said that he has the strength to run his company despite the current global economic crisis, and that he is turning the advantage of the crisis to himself. Mr. Hatanarachchi said that the aim is to increase the export and bring more dollars to the country."
      ],
